README.md
Dockerfile.builder

# Public dynclient module is distributed as its own Go module and is
# fetched independently by external consumers via `go get`. It does not
# need to be bundled into the server's embed.FS — and embedding the
# whole dynclient subtree would also pull in dynclient/baml-patched,
# which carries a vendored BAML runtime fork.
dynclient

# Monitoring/observability config (not needed at runtime)
monitoring

# Integration tests
integration

# Test files
**/*_test.go

# Generated framework adapter files (emitted at build time by
# adapters/adapter_v*/cmd/main.go and at customer-build time by
# cmd/build/build.sh). Source of truth lives in
# adapters/common/codegen. The pattern is module-root relative
# because cmd/embed evaluates .embedignore patterns inside each
# discovered module — only per-adapter modules have an
# adapter/adapter.go to begin with.
**/adapter/adapter.go

# Codegen test scaffolding (codegen/internal/fixtures and any
# future siblings). These are non-test .go files because the
# compile-matrix test's temp module must `go build` against real
# type declarations — `_test.go` files are invisible to `go build`
# — but they are NOT part of the published codegen artifact and
# must not be bundled into the server binary's embed.FS.
codegen/internal

# Codegen test corpora for the bamlfuzz property fuzzer.
codegen/testdata

# Golden/differential fixture corpus for the native output_format renderer
# (internal/schema/outputformat). The want.txt/bundle.json files are
# test-only parity fixtures, not a customer-build input — keep them out of
# the server binary's embed.FS, mirroring codegen/testdata above.
internal/schema/outputformat/testdata

# de-BAML Phase 3 slice-2 STATIC differential oracle fixture: the claimed
# .baml project (baml_src) plus its UNTOUCHED stock BAML v0.223.0 generated Go
# client (baml_client). This is a test-only oracle artifact consumed solely by
# the //go:build integration test in internal/nativeprompt/staticoracle; it must
# NEVER enter the customer/container source bundle. In particular the generated
# baml_client imports the stock github.com/boundaryml/baml runtime, so embedding
# it would make the root server binary ship a SECOND generated BAML client.
# Excluded here (cmd/embed includes testdata dirs by default — see
# internal/schema/testdata in embed.go) so the root embed manifest stays
# unchanged, mirroring internal/schema/outputformat/testdata above.
internal/nativeprompt/testdata/static_oracle

# bamlfuzz lives publicly under codegen/ (not internal/) so the
# root-module integration test can import it without coupling
# adapters/common to integration/testutil. The package is test
# infrastructure for the property fuzzer, not a customer-build
# input — keep the source out of the production embed bundle.
codegen/bamlfuzz

# Working notes used during in-flight feature scoping. The directory
# is untracked in git and only appears in some local workspaces; it
# carries no runtime semantics for the server. Excluding it keeps a
# fresh checkout's cmd/embed output deterministic regardless of
# whether the operator has session notes on disk.
notes

# Root-level command build artifacts. `go build ./cmd/introspect` and
# `go build ./cmd/schema` default their output to `./introspect` and
# `./schema` at the module root; both are gitignored (see .gitignore's
# /introspect and /schema) and are never committed. Excluding them here
# keeps cmd/embed's manifest deterministic regardless of whether an
# operator has a stray build artifact on disk — the same rationale as
# `notes` above. Without this, a locally-built binary is silently added
# to the root //go:embed directive and the manifest then fails on a
# clean checkout with "pattern introspect: no matching files found".
introspect
schema
